Struct vs Class:
  Same, except: Default visibility?
  Struct -> Public, Class -> Private (everything)

Function Overloading -> Allowed as long as Number of Inputs OR Input Types are different

Assigning Values:
  int a = 5;
  int b(6);
  int c = int(7); // Works for most of the types

Reducing # of Lines of Constructor[cpp]:
  Vector2D::Vector2D(float x, float y) : m_x(x), m_y(y) {} // Direct mapping of variables to parameters

Empty Constructor:
.h:
  Vector2D();
.cpp:
  Vector2D::Vector2D(float x, float y) : m_x(0), m_y(0) {}

Creating Instances:
  Vector2D v1;
  Vector2D v2 = Vector2D();
  Vector2D v3(5.0, 6.0);

Copying:
  Vector2D v4 = v1;
  General Prototype:
    Type(const Type &object); //object - to be copied

